sql:
SELECT AVG(pr.performance_rating) AS average_performance_rating
FROM performance_reviews pr
JOIN performance_incentives pi ON pr.emp_id = pi.emp_id;

external_knowledge:
High-performing staff refers to employees with a performance rating greater than 4; reward in this context means receiving an incentive, and it includes both the type and the amount of the incentive.;
Performance metrics include the performance rating and the incentives received.;
Positions refer to the job titles of the employees.

sql:
SELECT e.emp_id, e.first_name, e.last_name, d.dept_name, d.location
FROM employees e
LEFT JOIN departments d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;

SELECT emp_id, COUNT(adjustment_id) AS total_adjustments
FROM salary_adjustments
GROUP BY emp_id;

SELECT AVG(performance_rating) AS average_performance_rating
FROM performance_reviews
WHERE emp_id IN (SELECT emp_id FROM employees);

SELECT e.first_name, e.last_name, e.dept_id, e.estimated_salary
FROM employees e
INNER JOIN salary_adjustments sa ON e.emp_id = sa.emp_id;

SELECT first_name, last_name, estimated_salary
FROM employees
WHERE estimated_salary = (SELECT MAX(estimated_salary) FROM employees);

SELECT DISTINCT e1.first_name, e1.last_name 
FROM employees e1 
JOIN employees e2 ON e1.emp_id = e2.manager_id;

SELECT first_name, last_name, email, job_title
FROM employees
WHERE estimated_salary > (SELECT AVG(estimated_salary) FROM employees);

external_knowledge:
- "treasures hidden within the employee roster" refers to the detailed information about each employee;
- "identities" refers to their unique identifiers, first, middle, and last names, and email addresses;
- "financial forecasts" refers to their estimated salaries;
- "occupational nests" refers to their department names;
- "echo of their recent performance reviews" refers to the latest review summary;
- "latest baubles bestowed" refers to the most recent type and amount of incentive received;
- "keys to their communication vaults" refers to their phone contact information.

- "wandering souls" is a metaphor for employees;
- "requests for a journey" refers to leave requests;
- "awaiting approval" means the status of the leave request is 'pending';
- "active passports" symbolizes active user accounts;
- "valid compasses" represents active contact information;
- "compass points" metaphorically describes contact information types (e.g., phone, address);
- "actual values of these points" refer to the contact details themselves (e.g., phone number, address).
